> > Currently only manual download + gunzip + install目前仅支持手动下载 + gunzip + 安装
> 
> I can't resolve this by gunzip, it's already a ZIP package for me

My case is different from yours. The Marketplace API returns the vspackage with Content-Encoding: gzip, but VS Code's download logic does not decompress it before passing it to the ZIP extractor (yauzl).
Here's my evidence:
1. Response headers confirm gzip encoding:
content-type: application/vsix; api-version=7.2-preview.1
content-encoding: gzip
2. Downloaded file is gzip, not zip:
bash$ curl -L -o /tmp/test.vsix "https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/_apis/public/gallery/publishers/ms-python/vsextensions/python/latest/vspackage"
$ file /tmp/test.vsix
/tmp/test.vsix: gzip compressed data, max speed, from FAT filesystem (MS-DOS, OS/2, NT), original size modulo 2^32 9250244
3. Node.js https module does NOT auto-decompress Content-Encoding: gzip:
bash$ node -e "
const https = require('https');
https.get('https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/_apis/public/gallery/publishers/ms-python/vsextensions/python/latest/vspackage', (res) => {
  console.log('Content-Encoding:', res.headers['content-encoding']);
  let chunks = [];
  res.on('data', c => chunks.push(c));
  res.on('end', () => {
    const buf = Buffer.concat(chunks);
    console.log('First bytes (hex):', buf.slice(0,4).toString('hex'));
    // zip starts with 504b0304, gzip starts with 1f8b
  });
});"
```
Output:
```
Content-Encoding: gzip
First bytes (hex): 1f8b0800
4. After manual gunzip, the file becomes a valid ZIP/VSIX:
bash$ mv /tmp/test.vsix /tmp/test.vsix.gz && gunzip /tmp/test.vsix.gz
$ file /tmp/test.vsix
/tmp/test.vsix: Zip archive data
$ unzip -t /tmp/test.vsix  # OK
So the root cause is: the Marketplace returns gzip-compressed body with proper Content-Encoding: gzip header, but VS Code writes the raw gzip bytes to disk without decompressing, then yauzl fails because it expects a ZIP file.
This may be region-dependent — I'm in China (Beijing), which might explain why you receive uncompressed ZIP while I receive gzip-encoded responses.
Environment:

VS Code 1.111.0 (Universal), macOS arm64
Network: standard connection with Clash TUN proxy (also reproduced without proxy)

