# Root cause analysis
I traced the operations within `distributed`:
1. In `BroadcastWork::finish()`:
https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/2817bc774f1a092afc3954abb676683b6dca2de4/torch/csrc/distributed/c10d/comm.cpp#L25-L42
`copy_()` dispatches through `ADInplaceOrView` -> `VariableVersion::bump()`.
https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/2817bc774f1a092afc3954abb676683b6dca2de4/torch/csrc/autograd/VariableTypeManual.cpp#L386-L399

2. This same issue was actually noted in the old `DataParallel` broadcast:
https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/2817bc774f1a092afc3954abb676683b6dca2de4/torch/csrc/cuda/comm.cpp#L125-L143
And it was fixed by:
https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/2817bc774f1a092afc3954abb676683b6dca2de4/torch/csrc/cuda/comm.cpp#L196-L197
though `c10d::BroadcastWork::finish()` never got this fix. it does a raw `copy_()` back into the original tensors.

3. Buffer versions are passed to `autograd` in `BatchNorm`:
https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/2817bc774f1a092afc3954abb676683b6dca2de4/aten/src/ATen/native/cudnn/BatchNorm.cpp#L324-L329
`running_mean` / `running_var` are saved by the autograd graph node at forward (with their version number) even though backward doesn't use them for single backward. When autograd unpacks them at backward time, `SavedVariable::unpack()` checks the version (and throws the error when it expects a version exactly N-1 lower where N is the number of forward passes).

4. Why non-DDP works:
`cudnnBatchNormalizationForwardTrainingEx` updates `running_mean` / `running_var` via `at::maybe_data_ptr()`, a pointer. This doesn't go through the PyTorch dispatcher = doesn't bump version counters. Version stays at 0 throughout.

## Complete timeline

Step | Operation | running_mean version
-- | -- | --
1a | DDP pre-forward → BroadcastWork::finish() → copy_() | 0 → 1
1b | cuDNN BN forward 1 (autograd saves version 1) | 1 (raw CUDA update, no bump)
2a | DDP pre-forward → BroadcastWork::finish() → copy_() | 1 → 2
2b | cuDNN BN forward 2 (autograd saves version 2) | 2 (raw CUDA update, no bump)
3 | backward() unpacks from step 1b: expects 1, finds 2 | CRASH

## Suggested fix
Add `at::AutoDispatchBelowADInplaceOrView guard;` before the copy loop in `BroadcastWork::finish()`.  This skips the `ADInplaceOrView` dispatch key:

``` cpp
void finish() {
    work_->wait();

    // NOTE [ Version Counter in DDP buffer sync ]
    //
    // Dispatch below ADInplaceOrView so that copy_() does not bump version
    // counters on the destination buffer tensors.  Without this guard,
    // DDP's pre-forward buffer broadcast increments version counters on
    // module buffers such as BatchNorm's running_mean / running_var.
    // When the same module is forwarded multiple times before backward()
    // (e.g. GAN discriminator training), the version mismatch between the
    // saved reference and the current tensor triggers a spurious
    // "modified by an inplace operation" RuntimeError in autograd.
    //
    // This mirrors the analogous fix for DataParallel in cuda/comm.cpp:
    //   See NOTE [ Version Counter in comm.*_coalesced ]
    at::AutoDispatchBelowADInplaceOrView guard;

    // Copy the output of the broadcast operation back.
    auto output_tensors = torch::utils::unflatten_dense_tensors(
        flat_tensor_.front(), bucket_tensors_);
    TORCH_INTERNAL_ASSERT(output_tensors.size() == bucket_tensors_.size());
    for (const auto i : c10::irange(output_tensors.size())) {
      if (output_tensors[i].numel() != 0) {
        bucket_tensors_[i].copy_(output_tensors[i], /*non_blocking=*/true);
      }
    }
  }
```
