I dug a little more into it. Prior to jitting the kernel PyTorch ensures that all the input params are the same type (it's a limitation of how things are implemented). In this case, the common type is `float` so the `uint16_t` param is casted to `float`. A few layers down from `opmath_jitted_gpu_kernel_with_scalars`, the casting logic lives here: https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/1002d56b122737beb60bf93c9559bfddef34500e/aten/src/ATen/native/cuda/jit_utils.cpp#L507-L510

