The `result` is always 0. `zeta(?, 0)` is `inf`. This explains the output.

It seems like we're never passing the definition of `uint16_t`, `uint32_t`, and `uint64_t` to the JIT compiler which is probably the reason behind this https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/1002d56b122737beb60bf93c9559bfddef34500e/aten/src/ATen/native/cuda/jit_utils.cpp#L208-L248

