@malfet "I’d like to clarify that the core issue is the Inconsistency of the Error State across different execution modes.
Observed Divergence: For the same FP32 input, the CPU produces a finite result ($3.15 \times 10^{38}$) while CUDA produces NaN.
Inconsistent Behavior: As noted in PyTorch documentation regarding extremal values (e.g., intermediate overflows in norm()), while results may vary, the existence of the error state itself should be consistent. Switching execution settings (CPU vs. CUDA) changes whether an error occurs at all, which violates backend parity. This functional discrepancy goes beyond 'slightly different results' and warrants a re-evaluation based on the requirement for consistent behavior between backends."

I believe the problem is here: https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/2010e09590ef79d3d6fbb50ebd0e34a231b745ba/aten/src/ATen/native/cuda/ForeachBinaryOpList.cu#L441

The kernel that is launched to copy only looks at the dtype of the first tensor in the output tensorlist.

Note that the function checks if all the elements in the src are the same dtype but does not have a similar check for dst (`self`).

https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/2010e09590ef79d3d6fbb50ebd0e34a231b745ba/aten/src/ATen/native/cuda/ForeachBinaryOpList.cu#L420-L425

A very simple solution would be to add a check for the destination as well and use the slow function if it fails.

```diff
diff --git a/aten/src/ATen/native/cuda/ForeachBinaryOpList.cu b/aten/src/ATen/native/cuda/ForeachBinaryOpList.cu
index 227d42247e..134754e2cb 100644
--- a/aten/src/ATen/native/cuda/ForeachBinaryOpList.cu
+++ b/aten/src/ATen/native/cuda/ForeachBinaryOpList.cu
@@ -420,9 +420,15 @@ void foreach_tensor_copy_list_kernel_cuda_(
         std::all_of(
             src.cbegin(),
             src.cend(),
-            [&](const auto& t) -> bool {
+            [&src](const auto& t) -> bool {
               return t.dtype() == src[0].dtype();
             }) &&
+        std::all_of(
+            self.cbegin(),
+            self.cend(),
+            [&self](const auto& t) -> bool {
+              return t.dtype() == self[0].dtype();
+            }) &&
         _check_tensors_share_sizes_and_strides({self, src}))) {
     return at::native::foreach_tensor_copy_list_kernel_slow_(
         self, src, non_blocking);
```

