@Lucaskabela @atalman I have been able to get to the bottom of `torchrec_dlrm` issue. It turns out that https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/170724 is a red herring.  The real root cause is that benchmarking `torchrec_dlrm` with 2.10 RC needs `torchrec`and `fbgemm-gpu` built from source and and both of them are 3-year old https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/main/.github/ci_commit_pins/fbgemm.txt (yuck). That's the reason why `torchrec_dlrm`  has been failing in CI since forever.

On the other hand, when benchmark `torchrec_dlrm` on 2.9.1. I can pip install the whole list https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/171936/files#diff-9709e5db13aeac90c0312b2b8da34b37cf51242ec789ca959fcf1ba295a8da7aR823 and get the the latest version of torchrec`and `fbgemm-gpu` that are working with 2.9.1. That's the reason why it gives the wrong impression that the model regresses from 2.9.1 to 2.10.

Let me submit a PR to bump `torchrec`and `fbgemm-gpu` pinned commits to fix this. But we can cross this off the list now because this is not a real regression
